Package org.nerd4j.csv.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CSVConfigurationException
    Represents an error occurred during initialization due to inconsistent configuration parameters.
    CSVException
    CSVException is a generic error generated from CSV facilities.
    CSVInvalidHeaderException
    Represents an error occurred during the creation of a new CSVWriter caused by providing an inconsistent header.
    CSVProcessException
    Represents an error occurred during the manipulation of a CSV field.
    CSVToModelBindingException
    Represents an Exception occurred during the injection of a converted CSV field into the related data model.
    CSVUnrecoverableReadException
    Represents a RuntimeException occurred during the reading of a CSV source that leaves the CSVReader in an inconsistent and unrecoverable state.
    CSVUnrecoverableWriteException
    Represents a RuntimeException occurred during the writing of a CSV target that leaves the CSVWriter in an inconsistent and unrecoverable state.
    MalformedCSVException
    MalformedCSVException is an error generated from data found in CSV.
    ModelToCSVBindingException
    Represents an Exception occurred reading a field from the data model that has to be written into a CSV target.
